originlink.xlink:title: Qiʿat Däbrä Ṣǝyon Qǝddǝst Maryam / QDS

locationlink.xlink:title: Qiʿat Däbrä Ṣǝyon Qǝddǝst Maryam / QDS

donors.donor: wäyzäro Tǝbläṣ is mentioned as the donor according to Additio 3. ʾAskalä Maryam (possibly baptismal name of wäyzäro Tǝbläṣ?) is mentioned in the supplication formula in the heading of Text I. Many other names (e.g. Gäbrä Ḥǝywät, Fǝre Maryam, Zä-Wäldä Maryam) are mentioned in the supplication formulas throughout the Ms. The names seem to have been added later.

dcomments.dcomment: King Yoḥannǝs IV (r. 1872-89) is mentioned on fols. 9ra, 33rb, 40va; Coptic Patriarch Demetrius (in tenure 1862-70) is mentioned on fols. 35va, 50ra, 50va; Metropolitan ʾAtnatewos (in tenure 1869-76) is mentioned on fols. 33vb, 35va, 40rb, 50ra, 50va, 80ra, 98va. Fol. 123 originates from a different, older (late 15th or 16th century?) Ms.

txstates.txstate: The Ms. is worn. Many fols. are heavily stained with wax and dirt. The leather cover is missing. Holes in fols. 20, 30, 40, 48, 50. Holes amended in fols. 1, 2, 81.

bindings.binding: Two wooden boards. Two pairs of sewing stations.

bnothers.bnother: Traces of a leather cover are visible on the inner faces of the boards.

squires.squire: A(2/fols. 1r-2v) - I(10/fols. 3r-12v) – ፪II(10; s.l.: 7, stub after 3; 4 stub after 6/fols. 13r-22v) – ፫III(10/fols. 23r-32v) – ፬IV(4/fols. 33r-36v) – V(6/fols. 37r-45v) – VI(4/fols. 46r-42v) – ፭VII(10/fols. 43r-52v) – ፮VIII(10/fols. 53r-62v) – ፯IX(10/fols. 63r-72v) – ፰X(10; s.l.: 7, stub after 3; 4, stub after 6/fols. 73r-82v) – ፱XI(10/fols. 83r-92v) – ፲XII(10/fols. 93r-102v) – ፲፩XIII(6; s.l.: 1, stub after 6; 3, stub after 5/fols. 103r-108v) – XIV(10/fols. 109r-118v) – XV(5; s.l.: 5, stub before 1/fols. 119r-123v).

taunit.rl-info: Pricking and ruling are visible. Ruling pattern: 1A-1A-1A1A/0-0/0-0/C. Primary pricks are visible. Ruling pricks are visible. Structural pricks are partly visible. The upper line is written above the ruling. The bottom line is written above the ruling.

phandwritings.phandwriting: Careful. Smaller letters starting from fol. 120va.

rubrications.rubrication: Nomina sacra; names of the king, bishop and patriarch; groups of lines alternating with black lines on the incipit page of Text I; heading of Text I; incipits of the texts and their sections; musical notation signs; (abbreviated) directives for the ministers; some other words, e.g. ʾǝgle, ʾǝmzǝ, kahǝn, ʾǝmmare; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.

abbreviations.abbreviation: ይካ፡ for ይበል፡ ካህን፡ ይሕ፡ for ይበል፡ ሕዝብ፡ በእ፡ for በእንተ፡ ይዲ፡ for ይበል፡ ዲያቆን፡

otherdetails.otherdetail: - Fol. 123, inserted sideways, originates from another, older (15th or early 16th cent.?) Ms. Fol. 123r contains an excerpt from the apocryphal Acts of the Apostles (The Discourse of Dionysius the Areopagite, cp. BConAp I, 55, from [ንጽ]ሕት፡ እስመ፡ ለአ፩፡ እምኔሆሙ፡ መጠውዎ፡...; BConAp II, 43; Ap1 in BauGaH).

additional.cont: Fols. 1va-2vb: Supplications from the Daily Office (cp. MQ p. 295), chants from the Ordinary of the Mass (MQ, 1955 E.C., cp. pp. 49-50), partly unidentified.
additional.det: Chants from the Ordinary of the Mass (fols. 2rb-2vb) has been written in script of smaller size.

additional.cont: Fol. 2vb: Heading of Text I mentioning the name of the donor in the supplication formula.
additional.add: Fol. 2vb: ኪዳን፡ ዘነግህ፡ ዝነገሮሙ፡ በአባዊነ፡ ሐዋርያት፡ እምቅድመ፡ ዕርገቱ፡…
additional.det: The heading written entirely in red ink has been added later.

additional.cont: Fol.122vb: Donation note.
additional.det: wäyzäro Tǝbläṣ is mentioned as the donor, other family members are also mentioned.

extras.extra: - Omitted passages have been written in small script in the upper margin: fols. 8r, 31r, 34v, 35r, 72v, 73r, 80v, 83v, 85v, 109v. - Crude notes: fol. 1r.

txquiremarks.txquiremark: Quire marks are written in the upper left corner: fols. 13r, 23r, 33r, 43r, 53r, 63r, 73r, 83r, 93r, 103r.
